### Shoppe Admin Backend API Integration Tests
### Base URL: http://localhost:9001/api
### Description: Comprehensive API tests for admin backend system

@baseUrl = http://localhost:9001/api
@authToken = {{loginResponse.body.token}}

# ========================================================================
# AUTHENTICATION MODULE
# ========================================================================

### 1.1 Login with valid credentials
# @name loginValid
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "admin",
  "password": "Admin@123"
}

###

### 1.2 Login with invalid credentials (wrong password)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "admin",
  "password": "WrongPassword123"
}

###

### 1.3 Login with invalid credentials (non-existent user)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "nonexistent",
  "password": "Admin@123"
}

###

### 1.4 Refresh token
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{loginResponse.body.refreshToken}}"
}

###

### 1.5 Logout
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

###

# ========================================================================
# ADMIN MANAGEMENT MODULE
# ========================================================================

### 2.1 Get admin list (with pagination)
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin?page=1&pageSize=10
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

###

### 2.2 Get admin by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

###

### 2.3 Get admin by non-existent ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/999
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

###

### 2.4 Create new admin
# @name createAdmin
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "username": "testadmin",
  "password": "Test@123456",
  "email": "testadmin@shoppe.com",
  "phone": "13800138000",
  "roleIds": [1]
}

###

### 2.5 Update admin
PUT {{baseUrl}}/admin/1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "email": "admin_updated@shoppe.com",
  "phone": "13900139000",
  "roleIds": [1]
}

###

### 2.6 Update admin status (disable)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/admin/1/status
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "status": 0
}

###

### 2.7 Update admin status (enable)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/admin/1/status
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "status": 1
}

###

### 2.8 Reset admin password
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/1/reset-password
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "newPassword": "NewAdmin@123"
}

###

### 2.9 Delete admin (test account)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/admin/2
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

###

# ========================================================================
# ROLE MANAGEMENT MODULE
# ========================================================================

### 3.1 Get role list
GET {{baseUrl}}/role?page=1&pageSize=10
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

###

### 3.2 Get role by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/role/1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

###

### 3.3 Get role by non-existent ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/role/999
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

###

### 3.4 Create new role
# @name createRole
POST {{baseUrl}}/role
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "name": "TestRole",
  "description": "Test role for integration testing",
  "permissionIds": [1, 2, 3]
}

###

### 3.5 Update role
PUT {{baseUrl}}/role/1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "name": "SuperAdmin",
  "description": "Updated Super Admin role",
  "permissionIds": [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]
}

###

### 3.6 Assign permissions to role
PUT {{baseUrl}}/role/1/permissions
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

[1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8]

###

### 3.7 Delete role (test role)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/role/2
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

###

# ========================================================================
# PERMISSION MANAGEMENT MODULE
# ========================================================================

### 4.1 Get permission tree
GET {{baseUrl}}/permission/tree
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

###

### 4.2 Get permission list (with pagination)
GET {{baseUrl}}/permission?page=1&pageSize=20
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

###

### 4.3 Get permission by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/permission/1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

###

### 4.4 Get permission by non-existent ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/permission/999
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

###

### 4.5 Create new permission (Directory type)
POST {{baseUrl}}/permission
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "name": "Test Directory",
  "code": "test:directory",
  "type": 1,
  "parentId": null,
  "path": null,
  "icon": null,
  "apiPath": null,
  "sort": 999
}

###

### 4.6 Update permission
PUT {{baseUrl}}/permission/1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "name": "Updated Directory",
  "code": "test:directory:updated",
  "sort": 100
}

###

### 4.7 Delete permission
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/permission/56
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

###

# ========================================================================
# AUTHENTICATION & AUTHORIZATION TESTS
# ========================================================================

### 5.1 Access admin list without token (should fail)
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin?page=1&pageSize=10

###

### 5.2 Access admin list with invalid token (should fail)
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin?page=1&pageSize=10
Authorization: Bearer invalid_token_12345

###

### 5.3 Access role list without token (should fail)
GET {{baseUrl}}/role?page=1&pageSize=10

###

### 5.4 Access permission list without token (should fail)
GET {{baseUrl}}/permission?page=1&pageSize=10

###

### END OF TEST SUITE ###
